:INFO
The Negotiation Book That Reads Like a Thriller
Chris Voss spent years as an FBI hostage negotiator and wrote a book that uses \
those skills to explain every negotiation from salary talks to vendor contracts. \
I read it in four days and immediately used the tactical empathy framework in \
a salary conversation I had been avoiding for three months. The result was not \
what I expected, but neither was my preparation before I had read the book.

:NOTE
The tactical empathy chapter changed how I handle hard conversations.

:QUOTE [subtitle:Chris Voss, quotetype:PLAIN]
The most dangerous negotiation is the one you do not know you are in.

:JOURNEY
Applying Never Split the Difference
Chapter
Applicability
- Mirroring technique | 5 | Used same day | Simple to learn and immediately applied
- Tactical empathy | 5 | Listening reframe | Negotiation is listening not talking
- Calibrated questions | 4 | Opener shift | Changed how I start every hard conversation
- Accusation audit | 4 | Counterintuitive | Awkward to try but effective in practice

